Guinea Says First-Quarter Bauxite and Gold Output Declines, Cocoa Soars

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-06-14T17:42:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/guinea-says-first-quarter-bauxite-and-gold-output-declines-cocoa-soars.html
Production of bauxite in  Guinea , the
worldâ€™s biggest exporter of the ore used in aluminum, declined 1
percent to 3.9 million metric tons in the first quarter of the
year, according to the  Finance Ministry .  Gold output fell 16 percent to 192,440 ounces, while
diamond production climbed to 137,860 carats from 72,870 carats
a year earlier, the Conakry-based ministry said in a statement
handed to reporters today.  Coffee production was up 43 percent to 13,090 tons while
cocoa output soared to 8,010 tons from 840 tons a year earlier,
according to the ministry.  Production of  palm oil  rose 4.2 percent to 2,980 tons, the
fish catch fell 30 percent to 3,980 tons and electricity
generation slowed 3.6 percent to 147,364 megawatts, the ministry
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
